      "solution": "# Example solution\n\nmessage = input()\n\ndecoded_message = \"\"\n\nfor index, character in enumerate(message):\n    if character == \"\\\\\":\n        continue\n    num_backslashes = 0\n    for behind_index in range(index-1, -1, -1): # Iterating back from the char\n        behind_char = message[behind_index]\n        if behind_char != \"\\\\\":\n            break\n        num_backslashes += 1\n    \n    # The char is part of the secret if an odd number of '\\'s precedes it\n    if num_backslashes % 2 == 1:\n        decoded_message += character\n\nprint(decoded_message)",
      "statement": "Escape the Dark Lord's lair by decoding a friend's messages! Any escaped letter (preceded by a non-escaped backslash) is a letter in the encoded secret message. \n\nFor example, `\\gwa\\a\\thi\\er` decodes to `gate` but, `\\\\s\\a\\m` only decodes to `am` because the backslash before the S is escaped by another backslash. \n\nHowever, `\\\\\\s\\a\\m` does decode to `sam` because the backlash preceding the `\\s` is escaped by yet another.",
